/* Printing in Nano can be done in 2 ways:
*
* 1. Using `println()` to print with a new line:
*    This automatically moves the cursor to the next line after printing.
*/

println("Hey, look! A new line!")

/*
* 2. Using `print()` to print without a new line:
*    This keeps the cursor on the same line after printing.
*/

print("Hello, Nano!")